An MA thesis is an independent research project that corresponds to the requirements of this guide and demonstrates the student's theoretical and practical knowledge, skills to use particular sources as well as the ability to formulate coherent arguments and express them in writing. An MA thesis is a clear and synthesized research paper where a clear problem statement is outlined and where scientific methods are used to analyze the object of study.Objectives/eesmärkid:  A Master thesis is mandatory and to be themed to the European Union. The successfully competed course demonstrated students' ability to narrow knowledge down to the ability to draw up a Master level academic research in a particular field.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful defence of a Master thesis, a student will: - plan and implement a variety of activities to achieve the objectives; - find solutions to a variety of theoretical and practical problems; - critically analyze the relevant literature published in English, argue to demonstrate personal opinion, draw conclusions and generalize; - analyze the empirical material in selected areas; - fulfill the requirements to a scientific research and acquire competencies to apply various scientific research methods.
